post_text: Do you have any of these items?
shared_text:
Angeline Pesek Brown
October 24, 2019 at 8:53 PM ¬∑

Recently, Laura Lucas and I attended a workshop on better implementation of STEM in the classroom. We are looking to acquire "found materials" for a STEM cabinet in my classroom. As you go through your daily lives, if you run across any of the following items, we would love to have them: wood scraps, clean empty water or two liter bottles, shoe boxes, empty paper rolls, paper bags, ANY crafty items you are looking to get rid of, tissue paper, empty Clorox wipes containers, or wood dowels. Basically, if in doubt, ask, we will probably take it.
ALSO, we are looking for any old hand tools, nails, etc.

Thanks in advance!

The students at Gibbon are collecting items this year for the Food Pantry. We wanted to stress the act of showing kindness to others in our community. The food pantry will take any items, but shared that there is a higher need for paper products, personal hygiene and baby products. There are collection boxes by the elementary and high school libraries!
Here are the events going on at school the next couple of weeks:
Today is a 1:45 dismissal. The Board of Education will also be meeting at 5:30 today. Please note the change in time.
On Thursday, December 20th, the parent organization will be bringing in a speaker, Bryce Abbey. It should be a great motivator to hear the story of a local Kearney man.
Friday, December 21 is the last day of this semester! We will also have a school-wide ugly Christmas sweater day! Join in the fun! School will resume again on Monday, January 7th.

Gibbon Elementary Parent Organization
January 17, 2018 at 5:48 PM ¬∑

Junior Achievement is coming to Gibbon Elementary, and we need your help! The program sends volunteers/local business leaders into classrooms, who teach kids about financial responsibility, entrepreneurship, economics, career opportunities, and etc. Junior Achievement has 6 classes sponsored and needs volunteers for the classrooms. Would you be interested in volunteering this spring? The classes are 45 minutes, once a week, for 5 weeks. You would be provided with all the materials needed for the curriculum.

Please forward this information on to anyone who might be interested in helping. Below is a Junior Achievement flyer that gives more information. Please contact Ryan Carson if you have questions or are interested in volunteering. rcarson@jacobsenorr.com

Thank you!

Would you be interested in volunteering this spring? The classes are 45 minutes, once a week, for 5 weeks. You would be provided with all the materials needed for the curriculum.

Please forward this information on to anyone who might be interested in helping. Below is a Junior Achievement flyer that gives more information. Please contact Ryan Carson if you have questions or are interested in volunteering. rcarson@jacobsenorr.com

Thank you!
